  "body": "**Description**\r\n\r\n`reference.Spec.Hostname()` always panic if no `/` presents in the Locator.\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the issue:**\r\n```golang\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"fmt\"\r\n\t\"log\"\r\n\r\n\t\"github.com/containerd/containerd/reference\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\tref := \"test:1234\"\r\n\tspec, err := reference.Parse(ref)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatalf(\"fail to parse %s: %v\", ref, err)\r\n\t}\r\n\thostname := spec.Hostname()\r\n\tfmt.Println(hostname)\r\n}\r\n```\r\nCode available at [the Go playground](https://play.golang.org/p/8bFOGrdTmp5)\r\n\r\n**Describe the results you received:**\r\n```\r\npanic: runtime error: slice bounds out of range [:10] with length 9\r\n\r\ngoroutine 1 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/containerd/containerd/reference.Spec.Hostname(0x4986d0, 0x9, 0x0, 0x0, 0x0, 0x0)\r\n\t/tmp/gopath583841917/pkg/mod/github.com/containerd/containerd@v1.3.0/reference/reference.go:129 +0x80\r\nmain.main()\r\n\t/tmp/sandbox478338582/prog.go:18 +0x80\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Describe the results you expected:**\r\nIt should print `test`.\r\n\r\n**Output of `containerd --version`:**\r\nCurrent `master` branch or tag `1.3.0`.",
